In this remake of the famous zm_cbble_b4,one of Moo's masterpieces; while keeping the original gameplay, we added a new theme to it: space.

It also got new rooms, a mech warrior-like robot and trough the skybox you can see the ominous space ring from Halo games.

In this revamped version of cbble, you will find:

- 64 spawnpoints.
- Original gameplay that made cbble_b4 famous among zm maps.
- Some spots tweaked for balance.
- More rooms, with more cbble-like box spots.
- Complete new theme: now cbble is some sort of spaceship with a containment breach.
- Revised lighting for realistic looks.
- Optimized for low-end machines.

We already tested it ingame and the map is reported to be 100% bug-free!
Enjoy!

ZM_SORRENTO

I converted my original ZE map into a ZM version. But a lot of changes were made to make this map suitable for ZM. Read below for more detailed information.

Story: Your left behind after the humans escaped succesfully with the escape boats to Licciana. Now you must survive together with your buddies in the Italian city of Sorrento. Arm yourself with a shotgun and stay on rooftops!

Map info
Overall this map is a lot darker then the ZE version. This is because it follows the timeline of the ZE map. The night was about to fall in the original map so its only obvious that this map is darker because it takes place later.
This map is zombie favored. Which means that there's plenty campspots or places where you can build up barricades but each place is accesible via multiple routes. Better get ready to run. My survival tip: Buy shotgun, nightvision and stay on the roofs. There's a lot of ways to runaway too.....be creative and make sure you know your exits.

* 64 spawnplaces
* Multiple routes throughout the whole map
* Non-lethal water this time ;-)
* Access to buildings, rooftops and sewers.
* Small customised weapons at the seadome building (at end of pier):
- 2 shotguns with each 200 rounds
- 2 AWP's with each 50 rounds
- 1 M249 with 999 bullets
* Custom texture: My signature spray can be seen at some places in the map

Have fun and stay human!

- GARGANTUA

Major differences in the remake:
  • Few more surf ramps have been added.
  • A third tower has been added.
  • Few buildings have been renovated.
  • A better crane has been added.
  • Speed boost panels have been added.
  • The contents of some building is still somewhat reminiscent of the old building, but the others are just straight-up modified entirely to accommodate more viable spots.

_sText:
Map Description (_v2_0)

  • zm_skyscraper is a map that consists of skyscraper buildings.
  • Old version was not that good, so this is a remake. The map's general layout remain mostly identical, though there are some huge changes that are done.

Map Features (_v2_0)

  • There are a plenty barricading/defending spot for the humans.
  • Surf ramps, and speed boost panels to allow easier navigation between buildings.
  • It has 64 spawns (32 CT and 32 T).
  • There are few secrets, and there are three towers with no teleporters, so you probably need to surf or bhop to get there.
  • There are nine teleporters that will teleport player back to the roof of the building.
  • All players suffer no fall damage.

Please notify me should there be any issues within the map. Thank you!

A small but fun zombie mod map, that requires basic jumping and parkour skills. Fun to play with any number of players. If you fall, <del>you die</del>. Actually, you get teleported over to the small water pool, to prevent falling damage. However, players may get stuck to one another and !noblock may be required. Some areas are quite dark due to the sun orientation, however the entire skybox could change in the future. I hope you like the WinterPlanet sky. Credit for that goes to gleb_erilov. There's also a teleporter that takes you to another section of the map, which has no hiding spots. Just look for the green doors. On that section you'll typically have to rely on teamwork and your guns to keep safe. The map has a lot of custom textures, but they're packrated. No worries. :) I hope ya enjoy.

zm_siberia Map Statistics: 48 Spawns Cubemaps Radar Map 0 Secrets Sniping Spots In terms of features, this map is fairly vanilla, but the gameplay on it is different from other maps due to its sheer size, and it could be considered experimental. The map is a desolate and abandoned farming community out in the middle of Siberia, though it could just as easily be a place like Saskatchewan or Yakutsk... Any gigantic frozen farmland will do. To represent the isolation and the fact that it is indeed a very rural farming area, the map is enormous. It is fully ¼ of the size that a map can be made in Hammer, and takes about a minute to walk from one corner to its opposite. Why the hell did I do this? To change the gameplay. The camping spots are fairly generic... Mostly climbing spots, but some barricading inside the buildings. However, due to the sheer size, on this map it is actually worthwhile to use sniper rifles. Humans can camp the tops of buildings or out behind the snowy hills and trees in cover at the borders of the map with AWPs and snipe down the zombies. They'll need someone to cover them with a short range weapon though when the zombies begin to attack. Anyway, I don't know how popular this style will be, since no one else has done it before, so if you completely hate it and think it's a bad plan, that's fine. I just figured it'd be interesting to try. This map is best on a server with !guns or !weapons so that humans can switch to short range weapons when zombies get too close. Otherwise it's too dangerous to camp the outskirts. Questions & Comments appreciated as always.
